1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by DramaFever

2
00:00:31,450 --> 00:00:33,820
<i>Why isn't anyone helping me get up?</i>

3
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:36,080
<i>Why?</i>

4
00:00:42,470 --> 00:00:44,340
<i>Let's just end this here.</i>

5
00:00:44,820 --> 00:00:46,200
<i>This is too hard.</i>

6
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:48,920
<i>It's just too hard.</i>

7
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,470
<i>No.</i>

8
00:00:53,470 --> 00:00:55,090
<i>I have to live.</i>

9
00:00:55,780 --> 00:00:57,250
<i>I want to live.</i>

10
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:58,710
<i>Someone...</i>

11
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:00,350
<i>Someone grab me.</i>

12
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:04,350
<i>I want someone to grab me!</i>

13
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:44,590
How much do you think
this building costs?

14
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:46,540
Excuse me?

15
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:49,290
Do you think that there's
anyone out there

16
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,500
who'd want to exchange
their life for this?

17
00:01:59,130 --> 00:02:00,310
By any chance...

18
00:02:00,310 --> 00:02:02,300
Do you know of any
restrooms in the area

19
00:02:02,310 --> 00:02:04,310
where a lot of homeless
people frequents?

20
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,470
What?

21
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:27,320
I'm sorry, but the patients in this
area needs absolute peace and quiet.

22
00:02:27,320 --> 00:02:29,280
You cannot interview
anyone in this area.

23
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,530
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk is
admitted here, isn't he?

24
00:02:30,540 --> 00:02:31,800
Yes, he is.

25
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:33,800
Then I guess we can't do
anything else about it.

26
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:35,470
I'm sure he'll have
to come out sometime.

27
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:37,680
Let's just wait for him.

28
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:48,570
- Yes, Director.
- How's his condition now?

29
00:02:49,530 --> 00:02:50,780
Okay.

30
00:02:50,790 --> 00:02:53,030
Don't let him out of your sight
until I get there.

31
00:02:53,470 --> 00:02:54,850
Okay.

32
00:02:54,850 --> 00:02:56,820
Add him to the family registry quickly.

33
00:02:56,820 --> 00:02:58,430
But all the reporters
are there already.

34
00:02:58,450 --> 00:03:00,070
Reporters?

35
00:03:02,060 --> 00:03:03,650
There's Kang Ji Hyuk right there.

36
00:03:04,450 --> 00:03:06,930
Is it true that you're
Chairman Kang Sung Wook's hidden son?

37
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:08,710
What's the reason for keeping
that truth a secret all this time?

38
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:11,540
How do you think things will change as
you come on board as a new heir?

39
00:03:11,540 --> 00:03:14,100
When did you find out that you're
Chairman Kang Sung Wook's son?

40
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,990
Is that fact related to
your recent accident?

41
00:03:16,450 --> 00:03:18,570
What are you guys talking about?

42
00:03:18,580 --> 00:03:20,920
- Aren't you Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk?
- Kang Ji Hyuk?

43
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,830
My name is Kim Ji Hyuk.

44
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:27,270
<i>Ji Hyuk.</i>

45
00:03:33,830 --> 00:03:35,370
Ji Hyuk.

46
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:44,260
What a relief to see that you're okay.

47
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,600
I'm so glad to see you, Ji Hyuk.

48
00:04:05,470 --> 00:04:07,510
Do you remember anything
from your childhood?

49
00:04:09,260 --> 00:04:10,770
No.

50
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,930
I don't remember a thing.

51
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:22,790
Let's not rush anything.

52
00:04:22,790 --> 00:04:26,310
Once we come to terms with our own
emotions, and get used to each other

53
00:04:26,310 --> 00:04:30,670
I'm sure we'll be able to form a bond
as father and son, and as family then.

54
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:34,110
You understand what I'm
saying, don't you?

55
00:04:36,460 --> 00:04:38,340
No, I have no idea what you're saying.

56
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:41,420
Okay, I understand.

57
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:44,340
I'm sure you must be flustered since
that's the way I'm feeling right now.

58
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:47,690
What I'm saying is that we both should
take some time to get used to the idea.

59
00:04:50,820 --> 00:04:52,600
Get some rest for now.

60
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:57,340
What do you do for a living?

61
00:05:01,050 --> 00:05:03,700
You'll find that out soon enough.

62
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:06,760
Do I have a mother?

63
00:05:06,760 --> 00:05:08,650
Of course you do.

64
00:05:08,650 --> 00:05:10,110
Really?

65
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:15,830
- Does she know?
- Of course.

66
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:25,290
You should've just let
the sleeping dogs lie.

67
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:28,000
We're just going to complicate
everything for one another.

68
00:05:28,010 --> 00:05:30,060
I can't do that.

69
00:05:30,750 --> 00:05:32,930
Because you're my son.

70
00:05:43,650 --> 00:05:45,370
Because I'm your son?

71
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,820
What's the point of seeking me out now?

72
00:06:06,140 --> 00:06:09,010
Why are they getting so curious about
our family registry all of a sudden?

73
00:06:09,010 --> 00:06:11,100
I think they received a request
from the investigators.

74
00:06:11,380 --> 00:06:12,760
I think they must've
discovered something

75
00:06:12,770 --> 00:06:14,160
that may have been
done illegally.

76
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:17,210
Ugh, why now of all times?

77
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,250
Forget it. I don't
think we need to worry

78
00:06:19,260 --> 00:06:21,310
about it since the
office will soon change.

79
00:06:21,980 --> 00:06:23,950
Did you look into the foreign matters
that I told you to look into?

80
00:06:23,950 --> 00:06:25,900
Yes, I think we'll get an
answer from them soon.

81
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:27,180
You think it'll work?

82
00:06:27,180 --> 00:06:28,980
I think there's more than
a 90 percent chance that it will.

83
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:30,180
Is that right?

84
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:35,270
And one more thing.

85
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:37,330
That guy...

86
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:41,250
I want you to confuse him. Throw money,
women, and whatever else at him.

87
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:43,570
So that he doesn't have a chance
to think about anything else.

88
00:06:43,570 --> 00:06:44,700
Yes, Sir.

89
00:06:47,400 --> 00:06:49,360
That's the life history
of Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk

90
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:51,350
that we have of
him up to this point.

91
00:06:52,630 --> 00:06:55,210
Don't you rather that you didn't know
any of that?

92
00:06:56,140 --> 00:06:59,830
- Why do I have to know any of this?
- Because he's part of the family.

93
00:06:59,830 --> 00:07:01,910
He's someone whom you need to serve.

94
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,630
I started searching for Kang Ji Hyuk's

95
00:07:05,630 --> 00:07:08,800
whereabouts about a year ago
per Chairman Kang's orders.

96
00:07:09,220 --> 00:07:11,720
I found out about Kang Ji
Hyuk's existence very recently

97
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,560
and I was able to find
his DNA records purely

98
00:07:13,570 --> 00:07:15,420
by coincidence from
his recent accident.

99
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:17,950
That's the result of all my findings.

100
00:07:27,930 --> 00:07:31,330
I just prepared some things that
I thought you may need for the moment.

101
00:07:31,330 --> 00:07:33,800
Just let me know if there's
anything else that you need.

102
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:35,550
And one more thing.

103
00:07:36,430 --> 00:07:39,490
This is the key to the car
that you'll be driving.

104
00:07:39,970 --> 00:07:41,480
Let me know if the car
isn't to your liking

105
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,010
and I'll swap it out
for something else.

106
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,160
Are you trying to recruit me right now?

107
00:07:51,410 --> 00:07:53,830
You know how those sports teams always
gets the players whatever they want

108
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:55,240
when trying to recruit them?

109
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:58,930
Getting them an amazing place to live
with a fancy car to boot.

110
00:07:59,340 --> 00:08:02,370
There's no one in this world
who tries to recruit a son.

111
00:08:03,770 --> 00:08:07,850
I'm sure you guys can do all this
since that guy has so much money.

112
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:12,140
Anyways, this is nice.

113
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:13,680
Getting a chance to live...

114
00:08:14,790 --> 00:08:17,740
in an amazing place like this
for having met a nice set of parents.

115
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:25,800
Money sure is nice.

116
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:36,340
<i>I want you to bring that scoundrel
back here and rip his heart out!</i>

117
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:41,210
What floor are we even on?

118
00:09:08,430 --> 00:09:09,680
Crap!

119
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:17,010
Thank you.

120
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:21,010
For some strange reason,
I keep having to receive help from you.

121
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,610
Um...

122
00:09:24,850 --> 00:09:28,570
Call me anytime if there's
anything else that you need.

123
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:31,270
Yeah, sure.

124
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:33,460
But...

125
00:09:34,990 --> 00:09:37,030
What is it that you do for them?

126
00:09:40,820 --> 00:09:43,100
I'm an employee of Hyun Sung Group.

127
00:09:43,580 --> 00:09:45,730
I take care of
Chairman Kang's family.

128
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:47,910
Really?

129
00:09:47,940 --> 00:09:50,130
Then I guess you must get to see
those parents of mine pretty often?

130
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:53,340
- Yes, I do.
- Go give them a message for me.

131
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:57,370
Tell them that I'm
tearfully grateful for

132
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:59,890
buying me this grand
house and the fancy car.

133
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:05,620
The son that they just threw away
and abandoned for the past 30 years...

134
00:10:05,620 --> 00:10:08,420
is speechless with utter gratefulness.

135
00:10:08,420 --> 00:10:10,160
Please make sure to
relay that message.

136
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,730
Yes, Sir.

137
00:10:19,910 --> 00:10:21,670
Now it's raining?

138
00:10:22,870 --> 00:10:25,260
Well that's just depressing.

139
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:48,510
You told me to let you know if there's
anything else I might need, right?

140
00:10:51,200 --> 00:10:52,680
Yes, tell me.

141
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,370
What is it that you need?

142
00:10:54,370 --> 00:10:56,910
An extra umbrella so
that I may be able to

143
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:59,470
shield a lady from getting
soaked in the rain.

144
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,540
Dong Suk.

145
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:31,050
You're going to get up from that bed
as if nothing even happened, right?

146
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:35,020
I've been so afraid...

147
00:11:35,020 --> 00:11:37,630
and because of that...

148
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:41,110
I've never even once got to
tell you that I love you.

149
00:11:45,650 --> 00:11:48,060
So please just get up from that bed.

150
00:11:49,650 --> 00:11:52,100
I can't live without you.

151
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,730
Oh my, look who it is!
Ji Hyuk's here.

152
00:12:03,740 --> 00:12:05,010
Yes, it's me.

153
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:06,510
- Are you well?
- Of course!

154
00:12:10,070 --> 00:12:12,400
Why are you still following me?

155
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:14,380
It's my job to do so.

156
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:20,100
Mom!

157
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,190
- Mom!
- What are you doing!

158
00:12:23,190 --> 00:12:24,550
Get away from me!
You're grossing me out!

159
00:12:25,370 --> 00:12:27,860
Mom, do you have any idea
how much I've missed you?

160
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:30,080
- You must've been so worried about me.
- Don't' talk crazy.

161
00:12:30,080 --> 00:12:33,160
Why would I worry about you?
I'm busy enough as is with my own life.

162
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:35,520
Excuse me, but are you his mother?

163
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:38,470
His mother?
Mother, my butt.

164
00:12:38,470 --> 00:12:40,910
He thinks that all the middle aged
women in this world are his mom.

165
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:43,000
Especially if there's something
that he can gain from the woman.

166
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,310
I bet he probably has
more than 30 women

167
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:45,640
in this market alone
whom he calls 'mom'.

168
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,870
No, Mom.
They're just regular moms.

169
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:49,830
But you're my mom.

170
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:53,250
Stop kissing my face.
Hey!

171
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:56,280
Where and what have you been
doing these past few days?

172
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:58,860
And... who is this young lady?

173
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:01,400
Did you cause another accident?

174
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,900
Accident?

175
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:05,730
Yeah, I did.
A huge accident.

176
00:13:05,730 --> 00:13:07,190
You didn't.

177
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:11,350
- Before you're even married?
- Excuse me?

178
00:13:11,350 --> 00:13:14,110
Come on, Mom!
What do you take me for?

179
00:13:14,110 --> 00:13:16,460
You're painting a bad picture of me
in front of this lady.

180
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:20,830
Don't let her mislead you.
I'm much more virtuous than I may look.

181
00:13:22,030 --> 00:13:24,520
Mrs. Hong!
Mrs. Hong, Ji Hyuk is...

182
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:27,070
Ji... Ji Hyuk!

183
00:13:27,070 --> 00:13:28,860
Your Highness!

184
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:30,890
Please forgive me for
not having recognized

185
00:13:30,910 --> 00:13:32,950
your status to have
served you properly.

186
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:37,310
I swear to pledge the rest of my life
in your servitude, Your Highness!

187
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:39,540
What's wrong with you now?

188
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:41,990
I told you that I caused
a slight accident.

189
00:13:42,890 --> 00:13:45,010
- What is he talking about?
- Ji Hyuk is...

190
00:13:45,010 --> 00:13:46,100
You know the company,
Hyun Sung Group, right?

191
00:13:46,110 --> 00:13:47,210
Yeah.

192
00:13:47,210 --> 00:13:52,280
He's that Chairman's son! It's all
over the internet and the newspapers!

193
00:13:56,050 --> 00:13:58,820
- Is he serious?
- It's not a sure thing yet.

194
00:13:59,530 --> 00:14:02,310
But that's what those
people are saying.

195
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,480
There's something that
I have to show you.

196
00:14:10,560 --> 00:14:14,000
Is what I heard on the news... true?

197
00:14:15,770 --> 00:14:17,250
What is it?

198
00:14:17,670 --> 00:14:19,940
Is he mom's son too?

199
00:14:19,950 --> 00:14:22,980
- Or is he just your son, Dad?
- Your mom gave birth to him.

200
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:25,850
Honey.

201
00:14:26,310 --> 00:14:30,280
Madame Choi, he came from your womb.
You can't even remember that?

202
00:14:32,980 --> 00:14:34,690
This is crazy.

203
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:37,470
Thanks, Dad.

204
00:14:38,050 --> 00:14:39,710
You kept this a secret
for how many decades

205
00:14:39,730 --> 00:14:41,400
just so that you could
surprise me like this?

206
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:45,300
I sincerely thank you. It was the
biggest surprise gift of my life.

207
00:14:45,300 --> 00:14:47,240
Surprise!

208
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:52,390
What was the point of
lying to Jin Ah too?

209
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,580
Then you go tell
her the truth.

210
00:14:56,370 --> 00:14:57,690
Tell her that we smacked a perfectly
healthy guy on his head

211
00:14:57,690 --> 00:14:58,910
and lied about him
being our son just so

212
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,150
we could save
our own son's life.

213
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:03,020
Tell her that's how
evil her parents are.

214
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,710
Go tell her that.

215
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:08,580
Wow, this is like a scene
right out of a movie.

216
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,500
I feel like we're in a drama.
So they've

217
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:12,440
been watching you all this time?

218
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:16,120
Couldn't a document like this have
been forged if you guys had wanted to?

219
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,900
It's not like they were shot
in the head or something.

220
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:19,680
Why would they want to
claim you as their son?

221
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,620
What use could you be
to them when you've

222
00:15:21,630 --> 00:15:23,570
got nothing to offer
them but your body?

223
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:25,980
Don't you agree?

224
00:15:25,980 --> 00:15:29,220
If you have a hard time believing me,
I can get it authenticated for you.

225
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:37,390
Well... there's no need to go through
all that trouble.

226
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:38,680
Hey.

227
00:15:38,690 --> 00:15:42,210
I think others are right about that.
You're being suspicious over nothing.

228
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:45,560
You should just be grateful that
they even sought out a son like you.

229
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:57,840
<i>I told you that I'm too
busy to come tomorrow.</i>

230
00:15:58,650 --> 00:15:59,860
<i>What?</i>

231
00:16:00,800 --> 00:16:03,950
Why do you have to put it like that?

232
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:08,600
Forget it.
I don't need your chump change.

233
00:16:09,350 --> 00:16:10,420
You're the one who needs
to get it straight.

234
00:16:10,430 --> 00:16:11,510
I'm hanging up.

235
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:16,740
- How unbelievable.
- Who was that?

236
00:16:17,160 --> 00:16:18,970
That was Mr. Kim.

237
00:16:19,990 --> 00:16:21,330
Mr. Kim from the butcher
shop at the market?

238
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:22,690
Yeah.

239
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:25,190
When I told him that I was going
to take the day off tomorrow

240
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:27,480
he threatened that he wasn't going
to pay me my wages that he owes me.

241
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:30,190
It's not like it's a lot of money.
It's just 100,000 won.

242
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:35,740
Maybe we should just
buy his butcher shop.

243
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:38,530
I bet 20-30 million won
is all we would need.

244
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:44,350
Ji Hyuk, since we're just
sitting around here,

245
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:46,630
should we call up those
girls for a date?

246
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,120
Don't you think that
they'd go out on a date

247
00:16:49,130 --> 00:16:51,250
with us if we got them
