Look here, Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.

499
00:35:44,820 --> 00:35:48,090
Let me give you a piece of advice.

500
00:35:48,810 --> 00:35:52,120
But don't get your pride all ruffled up
where it's not needed.

501
00:35:52,120 --> 00:35:54,640
Take the money and
spend it all you like,

502
00:35:54,650 --> 00:35:57,180
and do everything you've
ever wanted to do.

503
00:35:57,610 --> 00:35:59,710
Buy everything you've
ever wanted to buy, and

504
00:35:59,730 --> 00:36:01,840
eat everything you've
ever wanted to eat.

505
00:36:02,350 --> 00:36:04,130
That's what you should do.

506
00:36:04,130 --> 00:36:06,040
Why aren't you doing any of that?

507
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:07,230
Why?

508
00:36:07,970 --> 00:36:09,720
Why aren't you spending any money
when they're telling you to?

509
00:36:09,720 --> 00:36:11,020
Spend as much as you'd like!

510
00:36:11,350 --> 00:36:12,880
I've never once...

511
00:36:13,530 --> 00:36:15,520
thought of their money as mine.

512
00:36:15,520 --> 00:36:19,820
That's why... that's why you're a fool.

513
00:36:20,670 --> 00:36:22,670
- A fool.
- Excuse me?

514
00:36:41,490 --> 00:36:44,450
Thank you for still being alive.

515
00:36:52,490 --> 00:36:54,200
This is a nice neighborhood.

516
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:21,420
Can you come over here and
help me pick one out?

517
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:33,660
I've never been overseas before,
so I'm not sure which one to get.

518
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:40,980
Um... why didn't you ever join
a girl group or something?

519
00:37:41,410 --> 00:37:42,900
Excuse me?

520
00:37:42,910 --> 00:37:44,410
I don't think it's
too late for you yet.

521
00:37:44,730 --> 00:37:48,160
You should start training or something.
You're a pretty good singer.

522
00:37:49,810 --> 00:37:51,770
What are you talking about?

523
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:54,710
- You don't remember last night?
- No, not at all.

524
00:37:54,960 --> 00:37:56,660
You must've been really
drunk last night.

525
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:58,390
I understand.

526
00:37:58,390 --> 00:38:02,720
Because I myself confuse my dreams from
reality from time to time when I drink.

527
00:38:04,580 --> 00:38:06,210
What do you think about this one?

528
00:38:10,950 --> 00:38:13,740
Let me know if you need anything else.

529
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:15,770
No, I'm all set with this.

530
00:38:20,250 --> 00:38:22,780
I forgot you told me to
go spend all my money.

531
00:38:22,780 --> 00:38:25,430
I should just blow all my money here.

532
00:38:25,430 --> 00:38:29,060
You called me a fool and
told me to spend all my money.

533
00:38:29,060 --> 00:38:32,910
Let's go. I'm going to blow
some serious money on you today.

534
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:35,820
No. I didn't tell you to
spend it on someone else.

535
00:38:35,820 --> 00:38:37,790
I told you to spend it on yourself...

536
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:40,560
So you do remember.

537
00:38:41,570 --> 00:38:43,050
You should've told me
that you remember!

538
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:44,570
Why are you trying to lie to me?

539
00:38:44,570 --> 00:38:46,140
Let's go. I'll show
you how I can spend...

540
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:47,740
No, please don't
be like this.

541
00:38:47,740 --> 00:38:50,510
Everyone can make a mistake or two
when they're drunk. Let's go.

542
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:52,090
I told you to stop doing this!

543
00:38:54,250 --> 00:38:58,250
- I was just...
- I'm sorry, but I'm working right now.

544
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,620
I hope that we don't make
things uncomfortable

545
00:39:00,630 --> 00:39:02,260
for each other
while I'm working.

546
00:39:03,540 --> 00:39:05,740
<i>Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk?</i>

547
00:39:06,960 --> 00:39:08,790
I'm Reporter Bae from WVS News.

548
00:39:08,790 --> 00:39:11,130
I met you at the hospital.
Can you give me an interview?

549
00:39:11,140 --> 00:39:12,420
- What do you think?
- Huh?

550
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:15,690
- What interview?
- I'm sorry, but we must get going.

551
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:17,080
- I just need a few minutes.
- No, I'm sorry.

552
00:39:17,080 --> 00:39:19,720
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk!
Wait!

553
00:39:19,730 --> 00:39:22,450
What did you and the
Chairman talk about?

554
00:39:22,460 --> 00:39:23,620
I told you that you
can't interview him.

555
00:39:23,630 --> 00:39:24,810
What did you two talk about?

556
00:39:24,810 --> 00:39:26,340
Where does your shares
stand compared to

557
00:39:26,350 --> 00:39:27,890
Director Kang Dong
Suk at the company?

558
00:39:27,890 --> 00:39:30,120
I told you that you
can't interview him!

559
00:39:30,730 --> 00:39:31,950
Reporter Bae!

560
00:39:35,620 --> 00:39:41,510
Don't you think that it's time for you
to make a move in your career?

561
00:39:43,350 --> 00:39:46,060
If a man like you came to
work for me at my company

562
00:39:46,060 --> 00:39:47,990
I have a feeling that we could be
quite successful together.

563
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:49,360
Sir.

564
00:39:49,370 --> 00:39:51,400
Why don't you just be frank with me?

565
00:39:51,770 --> 00:39:53,990
What is it that you
want to hear from me?

566
00:39:53,990 --> 00:39:56,710
I'll just be honest with you
since you're my junior.

567
00:39:56,710 --> 00:39:59,270
Why do you keep digging
around my company?

568
00:40:02,380 --> 00:40:03,990
You know a man by the name
of Jung Won Tae, don't' you?

569
00:40:03,990 --> 00:40:06,170
He was the prosecutor for
Seoul's eastern district?

570
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:09,130
- Yes, I know him.
- You owe him a debt, don't you?

571
00:40:09,130 --> 00:40:10,860
When he got transferred down to Busan?

572
00:40:10,860 --> 00:40:14,050
Are you saying that I'm responsible
for his transfer?

573
00:40:14,050 --> 00:40:18,720
It has been decided that he'll be
promoted to Chief Prosecutor.

574
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:20,580
Even though he's slightly starting to
dig around right now

575
00:40:20,580 --> 00:40:23,370
he's going to get serious about it
once he's officially promoted.

576
00:40:23,370 --> 00:40:26,840
I think it would be wise for you to
prepare yourself for a serious battle.

577
00:40:55,860 --> 00:40:57,260
Ta da!

578
00:40:57,260 --> 00:40:58,960
- Study hard, okay?
- Okay!

579
00:40:58,960 --> 00:41:01,170
Okay, next!

580
00:41:01,170 --> 00:41:03,560
- Thank you!
- You're so cute! How old are you?

581
00:41:03,560 --> 00:41:05,400
- I'm five years old.
- You're five?

582
00:41:07,660 --> 00:41:09,720
Study hard, okay?

583
00:41:14,430 --> 00:41:16,000
I want something else.

584
00:41:16,750 --> 00:41:20,370
- Just take what you're given.
- I want a robot too!

585
00:41:20,370 --> 00:41:23,090
I don't have another robot.
Just take the pink pencil case.

586
00:41:23,090 --> 00:41:25,430
I want a robot!

587
00:41:25,430 --> 00:41:26,760
You little rascal.

588
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,310
Give it back if you don't want it,
and I'll give it to someone else.

589
00:41:28,310 --> 00:41:29,450
Next.

590
00:41:31,960 --> 00:41:34,190
What?
Did you just kick me?

591
00:41:35,130 --> 00:41:38,690
Would you look at this kid. How dare
you glare at an adult like that?

592
00:41:38,690 --> 00:41:40,020
Come over here, you rascal.

593
00:41:41,350 --> 00:41:43,000
Hey!
Get over here right now!

594
00:41:46,960 --> 00:41:49,330
You've met your match today.
Come here!

595
00:41:49,330 --> 00:41:50,720
Come over here right now!

596
00:41:53,550 --> 00:41:55,870
How dare you act like I used to
when I was a kid?

597
00:41:56,380 --> 00:41:57,780
I'm going to drown
you with my kisses!

598
00:41:57,790 --> 00:41:59,210
Let go of me!

599
00:42:03,390 --> 00:42:05,030
My Sister Mom!

600
00:42:05,430 --> 00:42:08,100
This is not a lie, but I'm really
going to come here often from now on.

601
00:42:08,590 --> 00:42:12,790
No, it's okay. Don't worry about me,
and you just go live a happy life.

602
00:42:13,180 --> 00:42:16,090
Okay, always be healthy,
and I'm going to get going now.

603
00:42:16,090 --> 00:42:17,750
No need to see me out.
I'm going to get going.

604
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:19,520
Ji Hyuk, wait.

605
00:42:20,470 --> 00:42:22,200
I've been holding onto something
that may have helped you

606
00:42:22,200 --> 00:42:23,890
if you ever wanted to
search for your parents.

607
00:42:23,890 --> 00:42:26,200
But now that you've found your parents

608
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:28,880
there's no reason for me to
hang onto this anymore.

609
00:42:30,020 --> 00:42:33,330
I think this may have been in the bag
that you were carrying with you.

610
00:42:40,410 --> 00:42:41,570
<i>[I know that the
heavens will punish me</i>

611
00:42:41,580 --> 00:42:42,740
<i>for abandoning my child
at this place...]</i>

612
00:42:44,030 --> 00:42:46,030
<i>[But it's just too
difficult to raise</i>

613
00:42:46,050 --> 00:42:48,050
<i>this child on my own
without his father.]</i>

614
00:42:58,480 --> 00:43:00,510
Have you known about it too?

615
00:43:00,510 --> 00:43:01,850
Excuse me?

616
00:43:02,660 --> 00:43:04,360
I'm sure you were just doing
what you were told.

617
00:43:04,360 --> 00:43:07,330
I have an urgent matter to tend to,
so I'll see you later.

618
00:43:13,690 --> 00:43:15,660
What is this about?

619
00:43:15,660 --> 00:43:17,590
If you could just tell me
what this is about...

620
00:43:41,460 --> 00:43:42,550
Oh my goodness!

621
00:43:42,550 --> 00:43:44,820
- What are you doing here?
- Where's mother's room?

622
00:43:44,820 --> 00:43:47,050
- Mom isn't here right now.
- Is it over there?

623
00:44:23,870 --> 00:44:28,030
Hey... you! You seem to be
mistaken about something here.

624
00:44:28,540 --> 00:44:31,090
But we don't think
of you as family yet.

625
00:44:31,090 --> 00:44:33,870
No, you'll never be our family.
Do you know why?

626
00:44:33,870 --> 00:44:35,690
It's because you're trash.

627
00:44:38,560 --> 00:44:40,100
Take a good look.

628
00:44:40,100 --> 00:44:42,430
Do you actually think that you and I
look like siblings?

629
00:44:42,430 --> 00:44:44,760
No.
Not even close.

630
00:44:45,820 --> 00:44:47,350
Right?

631
00:44:48,160 --> 00:44:50,070
You don't think so either.

632
00:44:58,990 --> 00:45:00,860
What the hell is his deal?

633
00:45:04,110 --> 00:45:06,350
- Straighten that out.
- Yes, Sir.

634
00:45:08,630 --> 00:45:10,310
Yes, Lady Jin Ah.

635
00:45:17,340 --> 00:45:19,220
<i>The caller you are trying
cannot be reached,</i>

636
00:45:19,230 --> 00:45:21,120
<i>so please leave a
message at the tone.</i>

637
00:45:31,020 --> 00:45:32,730
- Yes, Director.
- What happened?

638
00:45:32,740 --> 00:45:35,460
Why did Kang Ji Hyuk suddenly
cause a scene over at the house?

639
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:39,730
By any chance...
did he catch on to what's going on?

640
00:45:41,110 --> 00:45:44,330
I think Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk discovered
something at the orphanage.

641
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:46,280
Really?

642
00:45:47,780 --> 00:45:50,260
Do you remember the thing that I told
you to prepare in case of an emergency?

643
00:45:50,260 --> 00:45:51,850
We need to get it ready in a hurry.

644
00:45:51,850 --> 00:45:54,300
Send out a team over to the company.

645
00:45:54,300 --> 00:45:55,460
Okay.

646
00:46:52,830 --> 00:46:55,460
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.
What brings you by here?

647
00:46:56,020 --> 00:46:58,270
Where's Chairman Kang right now?

648
00:46:58,270 --> 00:47:01,300
I'm actually trying to locate
where Chairman Kang is myself.

649
00:47:01,300 --> 00:47:02,870
I think he may be away
on a business trip.

650
00:47:02,890 --> 00:47:04,470
Can you get in touch with him?

651
00:47:04,470 --> 00:47:06,020
I'm not sure.

652
00:47:06,020 --> 00:47:07,180
I tried to reach him,
but I wasn't able to get a hold of him.

653
00:47:07,180 --> 00:47:10,550
He may be in the middle of
an important meeting right now.

654
00:47:11,170 --> 00:47:13,170
What is it that you
need to see him about?

655
00:47:13,170 --> 00:47:16,400
There's something
that I need to verify with him.

656
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:17,500
Why don't you tell me what it is?

657
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:20,220
- I can check for you when I see him...
- No.

658
00:47:21,950 --> 00:47:24,330
I'd like to speak to him
directly in person.

659
00:47:25,220 --> 00:47:26,770
I'll just wait for him.

660
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:36,780
Is there something...

661
00:47:36,780 --> 00:47:39,400
that you're disappointed
with the Chairman about?

662
00:47:40,450 --> 00:47:42,340
It's been quite a
while since I started

663
00:47:42,350 --> 00:47:44,260
working for Chairman
Kang and his family.

664
00:47:45,410 --> 00:47:46,780
There's something
that I've learned in

665
00:47:46,800 --> 00:47:48,180
all the years that
I've worked for them.

666
00:47:49,150 --> 00:47:52,290
All the members of that family...
are weary of other people.

667
00:47:52,300 --> 00:47:54,890
Just think about what it would be like
if you had just walked out of a bank

668
00:47:54,890 --> 00:47:56,760
with a huge bag of cash on you.

669
00:47:57,170 --> 00:47:59,920
You begin to be suspicious of everyone
who walks by you.

670
00:48:00,980 --> 00:48:05,880
Same goes for blood ties. No, blood
ties are even more suspicious.

671
00:48:06,400 --> 00:48:07,910
Because closer a person is to you

672
00:48:07,910 --> 00:48:10,080
higher the danger of that person
stabbing you in the back.

673
00:48:13,630 --> 00:48:15,530
You cannot expect...

674
00:48:15,530 --> 00:48:18,420
a normal family life
with people like that.

675
00:48:18,420 --> 00:48:19,920
Is that right?

676
00:48:21,270 --> 00:48:23,720
Then... why would people
like that falsely

677
00:48:23,730 --> 00:48:26,190
forge up a family
registry document?

678
00:48:28,100 --> 00:48:30,330
I have no idea what it is
that you're implying right now.

679
00:48:32,790 --> 00:48:34,590
Looking at you right now...

680
00:48:35,540 --> 00:48:38,310
I get the feeling that you know this
family better than anyone else.

681
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:41,120
Then I guess you must
know about it too.

682
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:44,200
What their true intentions are.

683
00:48:46,370 --> 00:48:47,890
Mr. Kang Ji Hyuk.

684
00:48:48,360 --> 00:48:50,480
You seem to be misunderstood
about something.

685
00:48:51,110 --> 00:48:53,930
But you really are
the biological son of Chairman Kang.

686
00:49:03,340 --> 00:49:06,450
There is only one reason why
anyone would show any kindness...

687
00:49:08,380 --> 00:49:09,890
to a stray dog out on the streets.

688
00:49:15,390 --> 00:49:17,480
It's so that they can devour the dog.

689
00:49:21,200 --> 00:49:22,610
Then what do you think
the stray dog in

690
00:49:22,620 --> 00:49:24,040
that situation must do
in order to survive?

691
00:49:26,190 --> 00:49:29,270
The dog must rip them to shreds
as they try to attack.

692
00:49:33,440 --> 00:49:34,850
That's the only way for
the dog to survive!

693
00:49:37,250 --> 00:49:39,890
- What is it that you want from me?
- This is all a misunderstanding.

694
00:49:39,890 --> 00:49:42,890
Do you know what kind of people
I hate the most in this world?

695
00:49:43,250 --> 00:49:46,180
It's those who deceives
me about my parents!

696
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:56,460
No, that's not true.
You must believe me.

697
00:49:57,960 --> 00:50:00,180
It seems as though
whatever you're hiding is

698
00:50:00,190 --> 00:50:02,430
more important to you
than your own life.

699
00:50:03,120 --> 00:50:05,540
Warn Chairman Kang for me.

700
00:50:05,540 --> 00:50:08,230
Because I'm going to meet him
to get the truth out of him myself.

701
00:50:11,090 --> 00:50:15,300
I'm not that generous of a person... so
you won't' get away easy the next time.

702
00:50:18,530 --> 00:50:19,680
He's...

703
00:50:20,790 --> 00:50:24,700
at the company's 48th
anniversary event right now.

704
00:50:50,420 --> 00:50:52,160
Is Chairman Kang
in there right now?

705
00:50:52,170 --> 00:50:53,910
No, he's not. But
Director Do is in there.

706
00:50:56,240 --> 00:50:58,040
<i>He's on his way there right now.</i>

707
00:50:58,040 --> 00:51:00,500
We don't need to explain
anything to him this time.

708
00:51:00,970 --> 00:51:04,710
Just make it clean...
and get rid of him once and for all.

709
00:51:24,970 --> 00:51:26,470
Don't go.

710
00:51:50,420 --> 00:51:52,130
Please don't go.

711
00:51:52,130 --> 00:51:54,180
I need to go and verify it for myself.

712
00:51:54,180 --> 00:51:56,090
I need to find out who I really am.

713
00:51:56,410 --> 00:51:59,000
Just who it is that I really am.

714
00:52:29,760 --> 00:52:31,160
Hold on.

715
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:50,030
Yes, I understand.

716
00:53:03,050 --> 00:53:04,620
Move!
Move out of the way!

717
00:53:45,690 --> 00:53:47,880
- Dad.
- You're here.

718
00:53:51,860 --> 00:53:53,420
What is it that you're
wearing right now?

719
00:53:53,420 --> 00:53:56,520
That guy came by the house earlier
and caused a huge ruckus.

720
00:53:56,890 --> 00:54:00,240
- Who did?
- Who do you think? Your firstborn son.

721
00:54:00,900 --> 00:54:02,720
Let's talk about that later.

722
00:54:04,730 --> 00:54:06,580
He's fake, isn't he?

723
00:54:08,080 --> 00:54:11,210
- Chairman Cha... you came.
- Yes.

724
00:54:15,450 --> 00:54:18,130
It's me.
We can't let that bastard go in there.

725
00:54:18,440 --> 00:54:21,060
Stop him. Stop him even if
you have to ram him down.

726
00:56:05,370 --> 00:56:06,850
What are you planning
to do in there?

727
00:56:06,860 --> 00:56:08,350
I don't know what I'm
going to do either.

728
00:56:09,780 --> 00:56:11,220
I believe that the
only reason Hyun Sung

729
00:56:11,230 --> 00:56:12,670
has been able to endure
the past 48 years

730
00:56:12,670 --> 00:56:15,110
was because of the efforts
put in by everyone at the company.

731
00:56:22,620 --> 00:56:25,390
A leader with the correct set of
principles and experience...

732
00:56:25,390 --> 00:56:26,970
and all the family
members at Hyun Sung who

733
00:56:26,980 --> 00:56:28,560
followed that leadership
with loyalty.

734
00:56:33,620 --> 00:56:35,300
I will do everything within my power

735
00:56:35,300 --> 00:56:37,400
to grow the strength
further to last another

736
00:56:37,410 --> 00:56:39,530
48 years, and longer
into the future.

737
00:56:40,620 --> 00:56:42,880
My Hyun Sung family...

738
00:56:42,880 --> 00:56:45,040
and everyone else who has
dedicated themselves

739
00:56:45,050 --> 00:56:47,220
to the further future
